results.name: Decimal expansion of first solution of equation cos(x)*cosh(x) = -1.
comment: This is an equation related to a cantilever beam: cos(x)*cosh(x) = -1. The first three solutions are: 1.875 (this sequence), 4.69409 (A076418) and 7.854757 (A076419).
link: Z. Guede, I. Elishakov, A fifth-order polynomial that serves as both buckling and vibration mode of an inhomogeneous structure, Chaos, Solitons and Fractals 12 (7) (2001) 1267-1298.
results.author: _Zak Seidov_, Oct 10 2002
